DEDUCTIONS ASSOCIATED WITH EMPLOYEE BENEFIT PLANS, U.S. TAXATION OF FOREIGN EARNINGS, AND VALUATION ISSUES REGARDING CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTIONS CLAIMED WERE $1,412 AT DECEMBER 31, 2004, AND $1,229 AT DECEMBER 31, 2003.

