DURING 2003, BCC AGREED TO RESTRUCTURE CERTAIN OUTSTANDING LEASES WITH ATA HOLDINGS CORP. (ATA). ATA ACCOUNTED FOR $705 AND $707 (6% AND 6%) OF OUR AIRCRAFT FINANCING

PORTFOLIO AT DECEMBER 31, 2004 AND 2003. THE TERMS OF THE RESTRUCTURED LEASES DID NOT RESULT IN A CHARGE TO THE VALUATION ALLOWANCE.

·

DURING 2004, BCC COMPLETED A RESTRUCTURING OF ITS LEASES WITH HAWAIIAN AIRLINES, INC. (HAWAIIAN). AS A RESULT OF THE APPROVAL OF THE RESTRUCTURED LEASE TERMS, BCC RECORDED

A PROVISION FOR LOSSES OF $13 DUE TO THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE APPROVED BANKRUPTCY CLAIM AND THE AMOUNT IT RECEIVED WHEN IT SOLD THE CLAIM. HAWAIIAN ACCOUNTED FOR $456 AND $506 (4% AND 5%) OF OUR AIRCRAFT FINANCING PORTFOLIO AT DECEMBER 31, 2004

AND 2003.

